The paper discusses structured evolutionary algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework can also be applied to optimization problems, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the benefits of using subpopulations, which is relevant to the field of machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG) as well as control systems (cs.SY).
